105854.name: Slippery Slope
105854.text: Freeze a character. Draw a card for each Frozen character.

106681.name: Snatch and Grab
106681.text: Destroy two random enemy minions. Costs (1) less for each card you've played from another class.
106681.flavorText: Snatch grabbed the snacks and Grab snatched the grub. The perfect crime.

106720.name: Snoozin' Zookeeper
106720.text: Battlecry: Summon an 8/8 Beast for your opponent. It attacks all of their minions.
106720.flavorText: You snooze, you lose (track of a very large and hungry panther).

107790.name: Snow Shredder
107790.flavorText: "Yeah dude, snowboarding is like, totally safe. I've only ever been injured once."

111485.name: Soul Searching
111485.text: Discover a card from your deck. Spend 5 Corpses to copy it.

110768.name: Spirit Peddler
110768.text: Rush Deathrattle: Reduce the Cost of a random minion in your hand by (6).
110768.flavorText: *facepalm* I asked for an art piece of a ghost on a bicycle...

105543.name: Summoner Darkmarrow
105543.text: Death Knight Tourist Your Deathrattles trigger twice. After you play a Deathrattle minion, destroy it.
105543.flavorText: Some people say your name can influence what career you go into. Summoner Darkmarrow is not one of those people.

105682.name: Sunsapper Lynessa
105682.text: Rogue Tourist Your spells that cost (2) or less cast twice.
105682.flavorText: Paladins are sooo lawful that they start feeling like a Rogue just by sitting on someone else's beach chair.

108348.name: Surfalopod
108348.text: Battlecry: The next spell you draw is Cast When Drawn.
108348.flavorText: Hi! Octopus expert here. This is NOT funny. Octopi only do this when they're extremely rad.

106675.name: Swarthy Swordshiner
106675.text: Battlecry: Set the Attack and Durability of your weapon to 3.
106675.flavorText: Everyone knows swords are slashier when they're shiny!

107822.name: Terrible Chef
107822.text: Battlecry: Summon a 0/2 Nerubian Egg. Deathrattle: Destroy it.
107822.flavorText: Anyone can cook! But not them.

106377.name: The Ryecleaver
106377.text: Battlecry and Deathrattle: Get a Slice of Bread. (Get 2 to Sandwich any minions in between!)
106377.flavorText: Legend has it that this dreaded blade is be able to slice through even the most stale of sourdough baguettes.

106373.name: Tide Pools
106373.text: Discover a spell that costs (3) or less. After you cast a spell, reopen this.
106373.flavorText: I know they look delicious but do NOT eat them.

106306.name: Tidepool Pupil
106306.text: Battlecry: If you've cast 3 spells while holding this, Discover one of them. ( left!) (Ready!)

105892.name: Tortollan Traveler
105892.text: Taunt Deathrattle: Draw another Taunt minion. Reduce its Cost by (2).
105892.flavorText: Tortolla, preserve my energy for this hike!

105795.name: Trail Mix
105795.text: Gain 2 Mana Crystals next turn only.
105795.flavorText: You can tell this is an escapist fantasy game because there are no raisins.

107928.name: Travel Agent
107928.text: Battlecry: Discover a location from any class.
107928.flavorText: I could've hired her or some Dodo.

110762.name: Travel Security
110762.flavorText: "You're just gonna let ANY 8-Cost minion get past you!?" "...Yeah..."

110859.name: Travelmaster Dungar
110859.text: Battlecry: Summon three minions from your deck that are from different expansions.
110859.flavorText: Our travel options will take you to Paradise and beyond!

109463.name: Treasure Hunter Eudora
109463.text: Battlecry: Go on a Sidequest to Discover amazing loot! Play 3 cards from other classes to complete it.
109463.flavorText: How hard could it be to hunt treasure? It doesn't even run away when you shoot it!

110844.name: Trust Fall
110844.text: Discover two minions that cost (5) or less. They gain each other's Attack and Health.

109323.name: Trusty Fishing Rod
109323.text: After your hero attacks, summon a 1-Cost minion from your deck.
109323.flavorText: That's weird… I can only catch magic carps with this old fishing rod.

105797.name: Tsunami
105797.text: Summon three 3/6 Water Elementals that Freeze. They attack random enemies.
105797.flavorText: Hop in, the water's cold! And angry. And alive.

110765.name: Turbulus
110765.text: Hunter Tourist. Battlecry: Give +1/+1 to all other Battlecry minions in your hand, deck, and battlefield.
110765.flavorText: "Passengers, we will be experiencing some minor Turbulus in the next few expansions."

106724.name: Twilight Medium
106724.text: Taunt Battlecry: Set the Cost of the top card of your deck to (1).
106724.flavorText: This twilight is too dark. And this twilight is too bright. But THIS twilight is juuuuuuuuust right!

110882.name: Un'Goro Brochure
110882.text: Draw two minions. Give them +2/+2. (Flips each turn.)
110882.flavorText: Our Un'Goro package includes the Tortollan travel tour! Just don't mind the Devilsaurs.

107850.name: Under the Sea
107850.text: Draw a different spell. Summon a random minion of that spell's Cost.

107771.name: Undercooked Calamari
107771.text: Battlecry: Destroy an enemy minion with Attack less than or equal to this minion's.

110753.name: Vacation Planning
110753.text: Restore 4 Health. Summon 3 Silver Hand Recruits. Draw 2 cards.

106444.name: Volley Maul
106444.text: After your hero attacks, get a 1-Cost Sunscreen that gives +1/+2.
106444.flavorText: "It's all fun and games until someone gets hurt." - LAME PARTY POOPERS

107824.name: Wave Pool Thrasher
107824.text: Battlecry: Give all other minions -1/-1. Deathrattle: Give all other minions +1/+1.
107824.flavorText: Used to be called Wave Pool Splasher until 'The Incident'.

106580.name: Weapons Attendant
106580.text: Battlecry: If you control another Pirate, equip a random weapon from your deck.
106580.flavorText: Hotel policy states that you must leave your weapons at the front desk. But GOOD NEWS! You can also buy weapons at the back desk!!

110772.name: Workhorse
110772.flavorText: Give me ONE reason why a horse shouldn’t be allowed in the travel agency.

108449.name: XB-931 Housekeeper
108449.text: After you use a location, gain 3 Armor.
108449.flavorText: "WHAT IS MY PURPOSE?" "You gain Armor." "OH GOD."
